00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:56,760
I really should reprint that criticism from Restak

652
00:44:56,760 --> 00:45:01,480
or hand it out, because it's this neurologist who says,

653
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:04,720
why is he telling us all these things about k-lines

654
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:11,080
and representations and so forth?

655
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:15,560
The answer is, he's from a community

656
00:45:15,560 --> 00:45:18,020
that doesn't have enough variety yet.

657
00:45:18,020 --> 00:45:21,960
And I'd be the first to admit that I

658
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:26,440
try to go overboard and think of five more things

659
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:27,760
than are in the literature.

660
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:37,000
But that emotion thing is nice.

661
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:40,200
Remember, that was a serious challenge,

662
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:46,440
because when I made that list, I do have a laser pointer

663
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:50,600
somewhere in my jacket, probably.

664
00:45:54,840 --> 00:46:00,640
How many words for at least noticeably distinct ways

665
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:03,720
of thinking, or reasoning, or figuring out,

666
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:08,080
or solving problems can you think of?

667
00:46:08,080 --> 00:46:12,160
Maybe there are 20 or 30.

