00:46:24,320 --> 00:46:25,800
Yeah?

671
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:28,200
Can I ask about your perception of free will?

672
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:32,640
And I got it from a reading that you don't have a strong sense

673
00:46:32,640 --> 00:46:34,680
of free will, and so what is that?

674
00:46:34,680 --> 00:46:37,920
I think it's the same as the one for consciousness.

675
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:40,700
Namely, it's a legal concept.

676
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:44,360
The idea of free will is completely obscene, isn't it?

677
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:46,760
What could it possibly mean if you

678
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:48,080
did something for no reason?

679
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:54,560
So it's a thoroughly empty idea, isn't it?

680
00:46:56,520 --> 00:46:57,920
Or what do you mean by it?

681
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:00,000
Do you mean there's nobody ordering you around,

682
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:02,760
so you're free to do whatever you want?

683
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:07,160
But of course, you're not.

684
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:09,920
