685
00:47:12,720 --> 00:47:14,200
In a sense, in the same way that you

686
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:19,080
draw in the fish diagram, the fish's actions

687
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:23,400
are products of the environment and of its current state,

688
00:47:23,400 --> 00:47:26,080
and it's essentially a Turing machine.

689
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:28,280
Well, it's some kind of machine, yes, sure.

690
00:47:28,280 --> 00:47:30,760
And so would you argue that we are also

691
00:47:30,760 --> 00:47:33,680
Turing machines that are just running out in the world?

692
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:35,880
Sure.

693
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:40,480
I've never heard of any even interesting alternative.

694
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:43,800
In other words, people who insist on free will

695
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:45,800
appear to me to be like people who

696
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:50,080
believe that there must be a god who created the world.

697
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:51,660
What's the next step?

698
00:47:51,660 --> 00:47:53,900
Who created the god?

699
00:47:53,900 --> 00:47:55,700
They don't take that step.

